WEBVTT

00:00:07.860 --> 00:00:09.340
Good morning.
Good morning.

00:00:09.360 --> 00:00:11.720
Good morning.
What are we doing?

00:00:13.100 --> 00:00:15.720
I've got a bad feeling about this.
We haven't heard a thing.

00:00:15.740 --> 00:00:20.220
Good morning.
Good morning.

00:00:20.300 --> 00:00:24.800
Good morning.
What is it? Seriously.

00:00:25.140 --> 00:00:28.041
This is super local for us.
It's our neighborhood.

00:00:28.041 --> 00:00:29.921
This is super local for us.
Ridiculously local.

00:00:30.641 --> 00:00:31.641
Cross that bridge and you're at my
parents' place.

00:00:31.761 --> 00:00:32.761
Exactly.

00:00:32.851 --> 00:00:39.851
You don't need to go that far, though.

00:00:40.381 --> 00:00:42.561
Cross that bridge and it's my parents'
house.

00:00:43.261 --> 00:00:49.361
So, the goal is Tokyo's symbol...

00:00:49.591 --> 00:00:50.591
Tokyo Tower.

00:00:51.941 --> 00:00:55.481
From there, to the east and west, or left
and right on the map...

00:00:55.861 --> 00:00:59.801
...you'll each start from points about
five kilometers away.

00:01:00.821 --> 00:01:07.181
On the way to Tokyo Tower, ask passersby
their political leanings. If they say right-leaning, turn right.

00:01:08.181 --> 00:01:10.981
If they say left-leaning, turn left.
This is insane.

00:01:12.461 --> 00:01:13.661
It's insane, right?
Yeah.

00:01:13.781 --> 00:01:15.861
You're really going to ask that?
Please do.

00:01:15.941 --> 00:01:18.101
Just regular people on the street?
That's right.

00:01:18.521 --> 00:01:22.142
This is crazy.
Come on...

00:01:23.222 --> 00:01:27.062
What are you talking about? I don't know,
but this is probably not okay.

00:01:27.142 --> 00:01:29.322
Yeah.
You can't do that.

00:01:29.802 --> 00:01:31.822
Also, at a crossroads...
Right.

00:01:32.142 --> 00:01:35.862
...you're allowed to go straight up to
three times in a row.

00:01:36.342 --> 00:01:40.182
I mean... I have a million objections to
this. But setting that aside for a sec...

00:01:40.402 --> 00:01:44.902
Even putting the whole left-right thing
aside, if you start going the wrong way...

00:01:46.442 --> 00:01:49.002
...it'll be hard to recover, right?
Well, that's why...

00:01:49.382 --> 00:01:55.202
If you want to go right, you just ask
someone who seems like that, right? No, no, that's the worst thing you could do.

00:01:56.102 --> 00:02:00.382
The pair that reaches Tokyo Tower first
wins. "First"?

00:02:00.382 --> 00:02:02.142
A battle?
It's a battle.

00:02:03.302 --> 00:02:07.842
Kitanakano are doing the challenge too.
The same one? Right now?

00:02:07.842 --> 00:02:09.322
From a different location.
I see.

00:02:09.362 --> 00:02:12.302
They start at the same time and race to
see who gets there first? Got it.

00:02:13.062 --> 00:02:16.883
I've never done anything like this.
What is that? No fighting spirit at all.

00:02:16.903 --> 00:02:23.663
We'll just reach the goal real quick, and
the rest can be "Kishi-Takano's Struggle."

00:02:24.503 --> 00:02:28.823
Honestly, I'm fine with that. I don't need
us wandering off for extra footage.

00:02:28.852 --> 00:02:31.423
I can't just do that...
You can. You're not busy.

00:02:31.423 --> 00:02:35.283
I can't. I don't even really understand
the whole concept, to be honest.

00:02:35.843 --> 00:02:37.443
Just vaguely, right?
Vaguely.

00:02:37.443 --> 00:02:41.963
Yeah. We don't even really understand this
whole right-left thing ourselves.

00:02:41.963 --> 00:02:45.503
We should really study up on it... Back in
my hometown there were lots of people turning right, though.

00:02:45.563 --> 00:02:49.443
No, no, leave that aside. What, are you
trying to walk away from everything already?

00:02:50.363 --> 00:02:53.503
So, what do political "right" and "left"
mean?

00:02:55.123 --> 00:03:02.083
The right generally refers to
conservatives who value long-standing customs and institutions, and want to preserve tradition and order.

00:03:04.103 --> 00:03:07.063
The left values freedom and equality, and
opposes domination and oppression...

00:03:07.643 --> 00:03:13.144
...as well as rigid hierarchies and class
systems. That's the usual definition.

00:03:13.924 --> 00:03:16.864
Then you're a leftist. Come on, seriously,
you should stop saying that kind of thing.

00:03:17.384 --> 00:03:18.384
Then you're a leftist.
Seriously.

00:03:18.384 --> 00:03:21.884
There's no such thing as just labeling
someone a leftist or a rightist like that. Takano from Kitanakano is a leftist.

00:03:22.264 --> 00:03:25.604
I don't even know if that's the kind of
thing you can say as a joke. Anyway...

00:03:25.704 --> 00:03:27.704
There's no "anyway" here...
So, which are you?

00:03:27.704 --> 00:03:29.024
Right.
Hey, come on.

00:03:29.664 --> 00:03:33.764
You can't really say either way.
No, neither.

00:03:33.764 --> 00:03:35.124
Right, right.
Ah, thank you.

00:03:35.124 --> 00:03:37.024
We'll give you a map.
Oh, we get a map?

00:03:37.104 --> 00:03:42.904
You'll use this map to make your way
there. We want to head toward Chuo Ward, so...

00:03:43.804 --> 00:03:45.104
Direction-wise, it's that way.
That way.

00:03:45.384 --> 00:03:47.984
Right.
Normally, you'd just go this way.

00:03:48.284 --> 00:03:52.064
Since directionally it's this way...
Well, at least roughly, if we just...

00:03:52.224 --> 00:03:54.704
We'll go something like this.
Try not to drift off course.

00:03:54.984 --> 00:04:01.124
And with that, both teams set off for
Tokyo Tower. Ah.

00:04:02.105 --> 00:04:06.265
So we actually have to watch this...
Looks like it'll take some stamina.

00:04:06.825 --> 00:04:12.965
Yeah... If you ask someone left or right
out of nowhere, will they even answer?

00:04:13.445 --> 00:04:16.405
It feels pretty hard to define where you
yourself fall.

00:04:17.145 --> 00:04:20.185
Like, for example, in the past,
capitalists were considered right-wing.

00:04:20.425 --> 00:04:25.025
And workers were considered left-wing. You
can see that from Britain's Labour and Conservative parties.

00:04:25.025 --> 00:04:25.985
But after that...

00:04:25.985 --> 00:04:28.065
More recently, as Thomas Piketty has
pointed out...

00:04:28.605 --> 00:04:31.725
...left-wing parties have become the
parties of wealthy elites...

00:04:32.125 --> 00:04:35.365
...while lower-income voters are often
said to drift toward nationalist conservatism.

00:04:36.065 --> 00:04:41.065
In Japan too, by the 1960s and '70s, there
was the far-left movement and talk of violent revolution...

00:04:41.345 --> 00:04:44.005
...so I think there was a fixed idea that
violence belonged to the left.

00:04:44.565 --> 00:04:46.705
If you go back further, there was the
Freedom and People's Rights Movement in the Meiji era...

00:04:47.465 --> 00:04:53.105
...which was actually a right-leaning
movement that included people like Itagaki Taisuke, but they also tried things like bombing and overthrowing the government...

00:04:54.125 --> 00:04:58.386
So it's hard to define neatly. And now the
question is why I'm rambling on about this by myself.

00:04:59.086 --> 00:05:04.206
What is this? I mean, I think people can
just say what they personally believe, but...

00:05:05.066 --> 00:05:09.626
Yeah, you really don't see this touched on
broadcast TV. If people think you are...

00:05:10.266 --> 00:05:15.866
...the extremists will get mad, so maybe
that's why they steer clear of it.

00:05:16.726 --> 00:05:19.086
I guess.
No clue what the strategy is, though...

00:05:19.506 --> 00:05:21.926
Still...
it does sound kind of fun.

00:05:30.823 --> 00:05:32.466
He looks right-wing.
No, no, no, don't do that...

00:05:32.466 --> 00:05:34.206
Don't stereotype people.
He looks right-wing.

00:05:34.206 --> 00:05:34.966
Not really.
A guy like that.

00:05:34.966 --> 00:05:36.046
Cut it out.
Someone like that...

00:05:36.066 --> 00:05:39.447
Stop saying that about random people.
But this is Shibuya, so...

00:05:40.287 --> 00:05:42.747
Young people probably aren't that...
Yeah.

00:05:42.887 --> 00:05:44.947
Maybe they don't care at all.
True.

00:05:45.027 --> 00:05:46.967
Neither right nor left.
If we went toward Yasukuni Shrine...

00:05:47.728 --> 00:05:49.988
Yeah, but...
The right-wing...

00:05:50.108 --> 00:05:52.448
If it's nothing but right-wingers, we'll
just keep circling. Then we'd only go in circles.

00:05:52.808 --> 00:05:54.388
I see. You're saying that awfully
casually, though...

00:05:54.428 --> 00:05:56.788
Is it okay to be saying all this?
No, it's not.

00:05:57.148 --> 00:06:00.349
So far, you're the one saying risky stuff.
Are they really going to use this part of us talking?

00:06:00.349 --> 00:06:01.689
If they do, that's bad.
If they air it.

00:06:02.809 --> 00:06:04.909
So what are you actually?
Right or left?

00:06:05.009 --> 00:06:07.669
Well, based on
how you described it...

00:06:07.669 --> 00:06:13.910
...I might be on the right.
Maybe.

00:06:13.910 --> 00:06:15.350
Patriotism.
Ah.

00:06:15.350 --> 00:06:17.230
I see.
I do have patriotism.

00:06:18.150 --> 00:06:20.991
Which is...?
Huh? Which?

00:06:21.051 --> 00:06:23.151
I don't have that.
That's not the issue.

00:06:23.731 --> 00:06:25.271
No, really, from what you said.
Just if you had to pick.

00:06:25.791 --> 00:06:27.011
Ah, Takano-san.
So this is...

00:06:27.011 --> 00:06:29.771
Hard to say.
This is our first crossroads.

00:06:30.311 --> 00:06:31.312
The very first one.
Yep.

00:06:31.792 --> 00:06:33.812
A crossroads.
You can go straight if you want...

00:06:34.912 --> 00:06:36.392
If you want to turn right or left...
Ah.

00:06:36.892 --> 00:06:40.252
...then you ask somebody.
Though we don't have to turn yet.

00:06:40.252 --> 00:06:42.133
First problem: there just aren't many
people. True.

00:06:43.193 --> 00:06:45.033
There's nobody walking around.
No way we're getting a left here.

00:06:45.073 --> 00:06:46.713
There may be even fewer people over there.
Yeah.

00:06:49.193 --> 00:06:51.853
So it's whether we go this way or not.
Right.

00:06:52.113 --> 00:06:54.394
H&M, huh. I feel like it'd be better to
hit the T-junction and turn right.

00:06:54.704 --> 00:06:55.704
Honestly...
Yeah.

00:06:56.394 --> 00:06:58.074
If we ask here...
Yeah.

00:06:58.894 --> 00:07:02.134
...and head this way,
toward the hotel district...

00:07:02.634 --> 00:07:04.695
...we probably won't be able to film
there. True.

00:07:04.835 --> 00:07:06.695
Because at this hour, there's no way we
can show people at a hotel.

00:07:08.195 --> 00:07:12.215
But if we go as far as H&M,
and then get a left-leaning person...

00:07:12.965 --> 00:07:13.965
...that'd be quite a swing.
Ah, true.

00:07:14.516 --> 00:07:17.216
Still, this route looks rougher.

00:07:18.226 --> 00:07:25.226
Which way are you aiming for?

00:07:26.317 --> 00:07:27.317
The right.
At this point...

00:07:27.317 --> 00:07:29.297
It's got to be right.
We are definitely going right.

00:07:30.763 --> 00:07:32.191
We're aiming for the right.
A right-wing person?

00:07:32.557 --> 00:07:35.317
Yeah.
We just want to turn right.

00:07:35.357 --> 00:07:38.458
Because if we say the right wing is
better, that gets messy again.

00:07:39.218 --> 00:07:43.578
At a glance, it's hard to tell who's on
the right. First we have to talk to someone.

00:07:44.378 --> 00:07:47.339
There are a lot of shaved heads around
here. A shaved head doesn't make someone right-wing.

00:07:47.339 --> 00:07:50.279
That's just prejudice.
Let's ask some young people.

00:07:50.279 --> 00:07:51.359
Hello.
Hello.

00:07:52.459 --> 00:07:54.499
Oh.
Iguchi-san.

00:07:54.499 --> 00:07:55.499
Iguchi.
Do you have a moment?

00:07:55.619 --> 00:07:57.639
A moment... They're probably nonpolitical.
We won't get anything.

00:07:57.639 --> 00:07:59.500
Can we ask you something real quick?
What have you been doing in Shibuya today?

00:07:59.500 --> 00:08:01.260
We were planning to go to Gusto.
Oh, Gusto.

00:08:01.260 --> 00:08:03.180
So you're on a day off, or...?
That's right.

00:08:03.420 --> 00:08:05.240
Take your time.
Yeah, just talking about stuff.

00:08:05.900 --> 00:08:08.080
Headed to Gusto?
Sorry to stop you on your way there.

00:08:08.200 --> 00:08:11.221
No, no, it's fine.
So what do you think? Like...

00:08:11.561 --> 00:08:15.361
For you personally...
You know...

00:08:16.141 --> 00:08:19.061
You know the whole right-left thing...
Oh...

00:08:19.161 --> 00:08:23.862
Right wing? Left wing?
Basically, the right means conservatism...

00:08:23.862 --> 00:08:25.182
Ah.
And the left is more like...

00:08:25.262 --> 00:08:31.443
He's really walking her through it.
...wanting to change things.

00:08:31.463 --> 00:08:34.343
Like a revolution.
So with that in mind, which are you?

00:08:34.403 --> 00:08:36.543
Uh...
The right.

00:08:36.543 --> 00:08:37.543
Oh!
Oh!

00:08:37.803 --> 00:08:39.023
So you're on the right.
She heard him.

00:08:39.543 --> 00:08:41.383
Ah.
Thank you so much.

00:08:41.383 --> 00:08:44.144
That seriously helped.
Thank you so much. That really saved us.

00:08:44.144 --> 00:08:48.544
Wow. Put a red circle on her T-shirt and
make it a Japanese flag.

00:08:49.044 --> 00:08:55.405
Meanwhile, Kishi-Takano also want to turn
right... This is bad...

00:08:55.485 --> 00:08:57.905
Oh man.
This is rough.

00:08:58.905 --> 00:09:01.205
This is bad.
We can't catch a single person.

00:09:01.485 --> 00:09:03.526
Can't get either right or left to work for
us.

00:09:04.666 --> 00:09:06.126
On top of how few people are out...

00:09:07.206 --> 00:09:13.206
...the question itself was such a hurdle
they couldn't catch anyone at all.

00:09:14.707 --> 00:09:19.667
Guess we'll just have to wait for Takano's
mom to walk by. My mom doesn't count.

00:09:19.767 --> 00:09:23.607
We can already see it from here.
Don't say that too loud.

00:09:23.747 --> 00:09:26.668
This is my hometown.
Think she's around?

00:09:28.068 --> 00:09:29.768
This is bad, seriously.
Ah.

00:09:30.148 --> 00:09:31.368
The rain's really coming down.
Hello.

00:09:31.708 --> 00:09:33.568
Hello.
Whoa.

00:09:34.288 --> 00:09:35.408
He looks nonpolitical.
You know them?

00:09:35.929 --> 00:09:38.389
You know them?
Tom Brown.

00:09:38.389 --> 00:09:39.969
You know them?
We're not Tom Brown.

00:09:39.969 --> 00:09:43.989
Lie if you have to, just talk to us.
Could you come over here for a sec?

00:09:43.989 --> 00:09:46.709
If you don't mind, can we ask you
something? Just a moment?

00:09:46.910 --> 00:09:50.890
No time?
And after ten more minutes...

00:09:50.990 --> 00:09:54.858
This is rough.
Sorry.

00:09:55.887 --> 00:09:57.958
Could we do a quick interview?
Please.

00:09:57.958 --> 00:10:00.138
Come on, say yes.
Thank you.

00:10:00.679 --> 00:10:04.919
He looks like he leans one way or the
other. After 40 minutes, they finally land their first interview.

00:10:06.979 --> 00:10:13.160
They want to go right, but will they?
We're out here asking passersby a question...

00:10:13.380 --> 00:10:18.120
Would you say your politics lean right or
left?

00:10:18.184 --> 00:10:19.756
That's the question we're asking people.

00:10:22.820 --> 00:10:24.340
I'd say left.
Ugh...

00:10:24.340 --> 00:10:25.781
I see.
Left, huh.

00:10:25.781 --> 00:10:26.721
Thanks very much.
Yeah.

00:10:26.721 --> 00:10:29.741
Left.
Isn't it over for us?

00:10:29.741 --> 00:10:30.241
Left.
Yeah.

00:10:30.241 --> 00:10:34.941
But at least up ahead it's a crossroads
again.

00:10:36.441 --> 00:10:41.002
We've definitely made up some ground.
The next one is the real key.

00:10:41.022 --> 00:10:44.802
Yeah. Westland got the right answer they
wanted earlier...

00:10:45.342 --> 00:10:49.323
...then went straight through three
intersections. And then...

00:10:50.783 --> 00:10:55.283
Okay, they're at the Omotesando
intersection. Here they absolutely have to go right.

00:10:55.563 --> 00:10:58.363
So going straight isn't an option. No,
straight is out. This would be the fourth time.

00:10:58.443 --> 00:11:02.664
So if you think of it the other way, going
left would send us way back. Right.

00:11:03.784 --> 00:11:06.424
So, interview time already.
Mind if we ask you something?

00:11:07.004 --> 00:11:10.784
We've been asking people a few questions
about their political views.

00:11:10.864 --> 00:11:17.365
Yeah. By the way, would you say your
politics lean right or left?

00:11:18.425 --> 00:11:20.445
I'd say left.
Whoa.

00:11:20.445 --> 00:11:21.445
Left, huh...

00:11:24.325 --> 00:11:26.326
Maybe wearing black means you're
left-wing? Well...

00:11:26.806 --> 00:11:29.186
Ah.
I mean, whatever, but...

00:11:29.206 --> 00:11:33.006
Don't say that.
We're literally heading the wrong way now.

00:11:33.666 --> 00:11:36.867
Our steps feel so heavy.
Walking in a useless direction.

00:11:36.867 --> 00:11:39.187
That's the one thing I didn't want to do.
What a nightmare.

00:11:39.247 --> 00:11:43.447
Wow, there really aren't many crossroads,
huh? So politically, are you right-wing or left-wing?

00:11:44.347 --> 00:11:45.347
Right.
Yes!

00:11:45.347 --> 00:11:47.707
Right.
It's not exactly a "Yes!" here.

00:11:48.027 --> 00:11:52.208
Even though they try to correct their
route toward Tokyo Tower...

00:11:52.268 --> 00:11:56.888
Hmm, I'd say left.
Damn...

00:11:56.908 --> 00:12:02.349
Damn... Once you get the wrong answer,
it's not easy to come back from it.

00:12:02.989 --> 00:12:07.649
That's the terrifying thing about this
right-left race. There just aren't...

00:12:08.929 --> 00:12:10.029
There are no people.
No people at all.

00:12:12.129 --> 00:12:18.230
Meanwhile, Kishi-Takano drew the wrong
answer at the start and have barely moved from the starting point.

00:12:19.930 --> 00:12:24.390
If we get left here, we can keep walking
for quite a while, right?

00:12:25.231 --> 00:12:31.651
If they draw left at this T-junction,
there are fewer intersections after it, giving them a chance to make up a lot of ground at once.

00:12:33.011 --> 00:12:38.252
Since nobody's around, won't we just run
into that same guy again? If we draw left, it'll send us toward Toyosu Station.

00:12:38.772 --> 00:12:42.072
Yeah.
We want left, but if we draw right...

00:12:43.052 --> 00:12:46.232
...we go back to the starting point.
Women do seem more left-leaning, though.

00:12:46.232 --> 00:12:49.453
What do you think?
Women seem more...

00:12:50.213 --> 00:12:53.713
There's nobody here.
We're doing a little interview, actually.

00:12:53.713 --> 00:12:55.193
So, anyway.
It's for a streaming show.

00:12:55.933 --> 00:12:58.353
We're asking people
about their political leanings...

00:12:59.113 --> 00:13:02.354
Would you say you're more right-leaning or
left-leaning?

00:13:02.854 --> 00:13:05.014
Even if you don't usually think about it,
just if you had to pick... Left?

00:13:05.014 --> 00:13:06.014
Yeah, left?
Left.

00:13:06.014 --> 00:13:08.374
Left.
Thank you.

00:13:08.394 --> 00:13:11.254
Is there a reason for that?
I just feel like Japan won't really...

00:13:11.714 --> 00:13:14.615
...get any better no matter who takes
over. Ah, I see.

00:13:14.915 --> 00:13:17.415
Ah. So that counts as a left-leaning line
of thinking.

00:13:17.455 --> 00:13:19.355
That was firmly left. Good.
Thank you.

00:13:19.355 --> 00:13:21.035
Thank you.
All right.

00:13:21.235 --> 00:13:22.955
Interesting.
Nice, thank you.

00:13:25.276 --> 00:13:27.476
That was a huge help. There are more
left-leaning people than I expected.

00:13:27.516 --> 00:13:32.016
That thing you said about women leaning
left... If we wanted to aim left, this might work.

00:13:32.396 --> 00:13:36.396
This will let us make real progress.
We can do this. Seriously, this is huge.

00:13:37.777 --> 00:13:41.337
Meanwhile, Westland keep detouring through
side streets.

00:13:41.657 --> 00:13:46.317
So, bluntly speaking, are you right-wing
or left-wing? Huh?

00:13:47.317 --> 00:13:48.317
Left.
Left.

00:13:48.317 --> 00:13:51.118
All right.
That means...

00:13:51.138 --> 00:13:54.298
That's good, isn't it? We can go straight.
